<title>USA: Barnert Hospital, N.J., cuts 45 employees -- paper.</title>
<headline>Barnert Hospital, N.J., cuts 45 employees -- paper.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Barnert Hospital in Paterson, N.J., layed off 45 employees on Tuesday, the Bergen Record reported Wednesday.</p>
<p>Hospital officials cited changes in the health care environment such as the increase in managed care.</p>
<p>The hospital employs about 800 people and is licensed for 282 beds. Lately, however, it has only been using about 200 beds, the paper said.</p>
<p>--Steven Dickson, 212-859-1652</p>
